cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.COM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the design and development of mobile communication networks, including the current 5G and the future 6G, and their ability to provide a variety of services.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper mentions the incorporation of new technologies like TeraHertz and Visible Light Communications, which are related to information transmission and processing.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper mentions future services like hologram interfaces, which are related to multimedia technologies.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also mentioned in the paper as a future service that will be incorporated into mobile communication networks, which makes this category likely.
- cs.COM (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the impact of mobile communication networks on society and the need for new architectures to meet future demands.
